00:07:03,000 --> 00:07:07,960
Now to the next phrase, a very common one, and specifically when you are not really sure
现在来看下一个短语，一个很常见的，特别是当你不太确定某件事，

171
00:07:07,960 --> 00:07:11,080
about something, but somebody told you.
但有人告诉过你的时候。

172
00:07:11,080 --> 00:07:15,200
Specifically in this case, Michelle says, I hear it's a wonderful city when talking
具体在这个例子里，Michelle说，“我听说那是个很棒的城市”，

173
00:07:15,200 --> 00:07:16,480
about London.
在谈论伦敦的时候。

174
00:07:16,480 --> 00:07:19,120
So what does she mean by I hear it's a wonderful city?
那么她说“我听说那是个很棒的城市”是什么意思呢？

175
00:07:19,120 --> 00:07:26,160
Well basically Michelle is saying she's never been to London, but she's read or she's heard
基本上，Michelle是在说她从没去过伦敦，但她读过或从朋友那里、

176
00:07:26,160 --> 00:07:29,820
from friends or from a TV show that London's a wonderful city.
或从电视节目里听说伦敦是个很棒的城市。

177
00:07:29,820 --> 00:07:35,560
So she can't say it is a wonderful city because she's never been there, but she can say, listen,
所以她不能说“那是个很棒的城市”，因为她从没去过那里，但她可以说，“听着，

178
00:07:35,560 --> 00:07:40,060
you know, I have, I have heard this from other people or from magazines.
你知道，我从别人那里或杂志上听说过。”

179
00:07:40,060 --> 00:07:43,440
So it's not even clear where she heard it, but that's not really important.
甚至不清楚她从哪里听说的，但这并不重要。

180
00:07:43,440 --> 00:07:48,880
So basically the idea is that we don't know personally, but we have friends that told
所以基本上，这个想法是我们个人不知道，但朋友告诉过我们，

181
00:07:48,880 --> 00:07:53,980
us or we have read in a magazine or a TV show, we've seen it, that it's great.
或者我们在杂志、电视节目里看到过，说它很棒。

182
00:07:53,980 --> 00:07:56,720
So you can use it with many things like a restaurant.
所以你可以用在很多事情上，比如一家餐厅。

183
00:07:56,720 --> 00:07:57,720
That's right.
没错。

184
00:07:57,720 --> 00:07:58,720
I hear the food is delicious.
我听说那里的食物很好吃。

185
00:07:58,720 --> 00:08:02,400
Or I could say, hey Marco, I'm going to Hong Kong Disneyland next year.
或者我可以说，“嘿，Marco，我明年要去香港迪士尼乐园。”

186
00:08:02,400 --> 00:08:03,400
Right.
对。

187
00:08:03,400 --> 00:08:05,920
And I can say, oh, I hear that it's a very fun place.
然后我可以说，“哦，我听说那是个很好玩的地方。”

188
00:08:05,920 --> 00:08:07,160
So Marco, you've never been there, right?
所以Marco，你从没去过那里，对吧？

189
00:08:07,160 --> 00:08:08,160
No, I've never been there.
不，我从没去过。

190
00:08:08,160 --> 00:08:09,160
Okay.
好的。

191
00:08:09,160 --> 00:08:10,160
All right.
好了。

192
00:08:10,160 --> 00:08:15,880
And to finish off, Mr. Campbell agrees completely about London being such a wonderful city.
最后，Campbell先生完全同意伦敦是个很棒的城市。

193
00:08:15,880 --> 00:08:18,880
And he says, I couldn't agree more.
他说，“我完全同意。”

194
00:08:18,880 --> 00:08:20,880
I couldn't agree more.
我完全同意。

195
00:08:20,880 --> 00:08:22,400
So he agrees.
所以他表示同意。

196
00:08:22,400 --> 00:08:23,980
We understand that.
我们明白这一点。

197
00:08:23,980 --> 00:08:28,640
But I couldn't agree more is like saying, I really, really agree.
但“我完全同意”就像是在说，“我真的、真的同意。”

198
00:08:28,640 --> 00:08:29,640
Right.
对。

199
00:08:29,640 --> 00:08:31,160
Like you are completely right.
就像你完全正确。

200
00:08:31,160 --> 00:08:32,160
Yeah.
是的。

201
00:08:32,160 --> 00:08:34,520
So this is a way to exaggerate.
所以这是一种夸张的说法。

202
00:08:34,520 --> 00:08:35,520
You know, you want to say, I agree.
你知道，你想说“我同意”，

203
00:08:35,520 --> 00:08:36,520
Eh, it's a little boring.
嗯，有点无聊。

204
00:08:36,520 --> 00:08:39,440
So you say, I couldn't agree more.
所以你说，“我完全同意。”

205
00:08:39,440 --> 00:08:41,720
I'm agreeing the most I can.
我尽最大可能同意。

206
00:08:41,720 --> 00:08:42,960
That's right.
没错。

207
00:08:42,960 --> 00:08:47,880
And then we can also use the opposite, which would be if you disagree with someone.
然后我们也可以用相反的说法，就是当你不同意某人时。

208
00:08:47,880 --> 00:08:50,040
I couldn't disagree more.
我完全不同意。

209
00:08:50,040 --> 00:08:51,840
So you just change that one word.
所以你只需要改一个词。

210
00:08:51,840 --> 00:08:53,520
I couldn't disagree more.
我完全不同意。

211
00:08:53,520 --> 00:08:54,960
So maybe I don't like London.
所以也许我不喜欢伦敦。

212
00:08:54,960 --> 00:08:57,440
Maybe it's too rainy or too dark for me.
也许对我来说它太阴雨或太阴暗了。

213
00:08:57,440 --> 00:08:59,200
So I say, I couldn't disagree more.
所以我说，“我完全不同意。”

214
00:08:59,200 --> 00:09:01,640
I think London is terrible.
我觉得伦敦很糟糕。

215
00:09:01,640 --> 00:09:05,480
Maybe not the right thing to say in a small talk situation, but we can talk about that
在闲聊场合说这个可能不太合适，但我们可以稍后讨论。

216
00:09:05,480 --> 00:09:06,480
in a minute.
稍后再说。

217
00:09:06,480 --> 00:09:07,480
Exactly.
没错。

218
00:09:07,480 --> 00:09:08,480
All right.
好了。

219
00:09:08,480 --> 00:09:10,480
So let's review everything one last time.
那么让我们最后再复习一遍所有内容。

220
00:09:10,480 --> 00:09:19,720
Hi, ladies.
嗨，女士们。

221
00:09:19,720 --> 00:09:20,720
Thanks for picking me up.
谢谢你们来接我。

222
00:09:20,720 --> 00:09:22,920
It's awful weather out there.
外面天气真糟糕。

223
00:09:22,920 --> 00:09:24,540
Absolutely.
确实。

224
00:09:24,540 --> 00:09:26,560
It's been raining for hours.
已经下了好几个小时的雨了。

225
00:09:26,560 --> 00:09:27,560
How are you, Melissa?
你好吗，Melissa？

226
00:09:27,560 --> 00:09:28,560
Are you okay?
你还好吗？

227
00:09:28,560 --> 00:09:29,560
I'm great.
我很好。

228
00:09:29,560 --> 00:09:30,560
Thanks, Mr. Campbell.
谢谢，Campbell先生。

229
00:09:30,560 --> 00:09:33,240
Do you have any business trips plans in Mr. Campbell?
Campbell先生，你有什么商务旅行计划吗？

230
00:09:33,240 --> 00:09:34,240
Of course.
当然。

231
00:09:34,240 --> 00:09:35,240
I'm always traveling.
我总是在旅行。

232
00:09:35,240 --> 00:09:38,160
I'm leaving for London next Monday, and then I'll fly to Boston from there.
我下周一要去伦敦，然后从那里飞往波士顿。

233
00:09:38,160 --> 00:09:40,120
It's going to be a busy month.
这个月会很忙。

234
00:09:40,120 --> 00:09:41,760
How about you, Michelle?
你呢，Michelle？

235
00:09:41,760 --> 00:09:43,400
Do you have any vacation plans?
你有什么度假计划吗？

236
00:09:43,400 --> 00:09:44,400
Yes.
是的。

237
00:09:44,400 --> 00:09:48,600
Mike and I will travel to Beijing to see Mike's parents for the spring festival, and hopefully
Mike和我将去北京看望Mike的父母过春节，希望

238
00:09:48,600 --> 00:09:50,360
next year we will visit London.
明年我们能去伦敦。

239
00:09:50,360 --> 00:09:51,840
I hear it's a wonderful city.
我听说那是个很棒的城市。

240
00:09:51,840 --> 00:09:53,400
I couldn't agree more.
我完全同意。

241
00:09:53,400 --> 00:09:54,960
London is really fantastic.
伦敦真是太棒了。

242
00:09:54,960 --> 00:09:55,960
It's my favorite city.
它是我最喜欢的城市。

243
00:09:55,960 --> 00:09:58,160
I'm sure you'll have a great time.
我相信你一定会玩得很开心。

244
00:09:58,160 --> 00:10:00,920
All right.
好的。

245
00:10:00,920 --> 00:10:04,000
So this is our last podcast all about small talk.
所以这是我们最后一期关于闲聊的播客。

246
00:10:04,000 --> 00:10:05,440
And I hope it's been useful.
我希望它对你有所帮助。

247
00:10:05,440 --> 00:10:09,880
We've gotten some great feedback about the different topics and small conversations you
我们收到了很多关于不同话题和简短对话的反馈，这些对话可以让你和陌生人、同事、朋友之间避免那种尴尬的沉默。

248
00:10:09,880 --> 00:10:15,920
can have with a stranger, a co-worker, a friend, to kind of not have that awkward silence.
没错。

249
00:10:15,920 --> 00:10:16,920
That's right.
没错。

250
00:10:16,920 --> 00:10:19,320
We've gone over a lot of different situations.
我们讨论了很多不同的场景。

251
00:10:19,320 --> 00:10:24,160
We've had situations with strangers, situations with work friends.
我们有和陌生人打交道的场景，也有和工作伙伴相处的场景。

252
00:10:24,160 --> 00:10:28,640
But I think what's really important is that in all of these situations, we're very polite.
但我认为最重要的是，在所有这些场景中，我们都表现得很有礼貌。

253
00:10:28,640 --> 00:10:30,440
We say nice things.
我们说些好听的话。

254
00:10:30,440 --> 00:10:35,560
There are these transitions like I hear or I couldn't agree more.
还有一些过渡语，比如“我听说”或“我完全同意”。

255
00:10:35,560 --> 00:10:40,080
These are wonderful ways of really being nice to the person you're talking to.
这些都是对你交谈对象表示友好的绝佳方式。

256
00:10:40,080 --> 00:10:41,080
That's right.
没错。

257
00:10:41,080 --> 00:10:42,800
And we're going to come out with a new series soon.
我们很快会推出一个新系列。

258
00:10:42,800 --> 00:10:45,040
So we would really like your feedback.
所以我们非常希望得到你的反馈。

259
